The best place in town for a quiet beer or glass of wine with friends. You can play board games or foosball, there's trivia on Mondays, Language Exchange on Thursdays, stand up comedy on Tuesdays, there's always something to do and new people to meet. Go early (they open at 5pm) if you want to have a sandwich and soak up the ac and free wifi. Friendly and welcoming staff. Dogs are welcome on the patio outside.

I've never walked into a place after the first time and had the bartender remember--and call me--by name.  The staff make you feel like you're part of the neighborhood bar.  There are good indoor and outdoor sections and nooks for varying degrees of desired privacy.  They even have TVs where patrons hook up their Switch for Smash.  Their tankards are an excellent value and I get one every time.  I have yet to try their food, but everytime I see someone with a dish it looks amazing.  Word of warning: there is VERY little space to park and maneuver around in front.  If you're not careful you can break a tail light.  Recommend parking across the street by the courthouse after 5:00 pm.

I've been going here for many years and always have a good experience. They have a great beer selection at reasonable prices. They have a large selection of card and board games as well as a fooseball table. There is an outdoor area with a small stage and tables in a patio area. They have a small selection of food such as sandwiches and hotdogs. Overall this is a great place and one of my favorite bars in Gainesville.

The Midnight has been around Gainesville for a while. They have comfortable indoor and outdoor seating.  Their beer and wine and section is not huge, however, this is a very fun place that meet up and have a drink or two. Definitely worth a visit- Thursday through Saturday are busy but the week days are not bad.

The Midnight is my home when I don't want to be stuck at home. The staff are always wonderful, no matter how swamped they get, the food is good, and the beer is always cold. They have something going on most days, and the first Wednesday of the month is Shanty Night. Go here and give give em your money.

The unofficial official nerd bar in Gainesville. A low-key but always fun, "regular" spot that will give you a lot of reasons to keep coming back. Midnight is one of the  few bars downtown with dedicated parking, and even if it fills up --parking is free and easy at the courthouse right across the street. Excellent location for multi-tiered nights - the Hippodrome, some of the best restaurants, music venues (CMC and High Dive) are all within perfect walking distance. I started going here the first week it was open when I was still a little Gator baby, moved away for five years and always made a stop on my return visits. Now I live in Gainesville again and it's my after-work brew spot. Love 'em.

Ya know, it's interesting - whenever I go out when I'm back home in Gainesville for holidays, I always somehow end up at The Midnight.  That's not a complaint, by the way, it's just a weird phenomenon I've noticed. I grew up in Gainesville, and have since moved away, and generally don't have much good to say about the city. Especially its bars, which are neither terribly affordable, nor creative or competent in their selections. But The Midnight always has a nice calm atmosphere, usually some quirky event going on, and a selection of good tasty beers for not much money.  Somehow, I always end up back at the Midnight. And I am always glad to be there when I do.
